<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 1:38PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Appomattox and north central Charlotte Counties through 230 PM EDT...
At 138 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pamplin City, or near Red House, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Appomattox...
Bent Creek...
Pamplin City...
Madisonville...
Appomattox National Historic Park...
Hixburg...
and Oakville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
